The paper is about visual object tracking, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses statistical modeling techniques, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses theoretical and practical aspects of the different appearance models, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of visual object tracking in visual surveillance, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics).
